text.tspan: Centralized infrastructure provides the most value
uncertainty and that makes it harder to allocate
large sums of capital to fixed infrastructure.
The value of distributed systems tends to grow
as new distributed technologies are added and
then build on each other. They are not capital

tspan.tspan: Blender, FreeCAD, IFC, and Ethereum are newer distributed technologies. Perhaps as soon as 2035,
the value of distributed technologies could match that of central infrastructure in some regions.
